HEADWORD: Maleic
<hw>Ma*le"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mal⟦eacute⟧ique</ets>. See <er>Malic</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid of the
ethylene series (maleic acid), metameric with fumaric acid and obtained
by heating malic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

